assetProfile.longBusinessSummary: Kanda Holdings Co.,Ltd., through its subsidiaries, provides integrated logistics services in Japan and internationally. The company engages in the general motor truck transportation, special loading motor truck transportation, light and specified motor truck transportation, consigned freight forwarding, and packaging and storage businesses. It also provides automobile maintenance, security, warehousing, information provision service and consulting, financial leasing, custom brokerage, port and maritime transportation, and proxy driving services. In addition, the company is involved in the leasing, brokerage, consulting, management, and sale of real estate properties; casualty and life insurance agency businesses; industrial waste collection, transportation, and disposal activities; vehicle operation control and inspection activities, as well as maintenance contract works; and contract development, systems consulting, sales, leasing, rental, and brokerage of software and its related devices. Further, the company manages dispensing pharmacies, restaurants, and parking lots; and generates and sells electricity. Additionally, it manufactures, sells, imports, and exports automobiles, computers, communication devices, clothing, convenience goods, food products, pharmaceuticals and quasi-drugs, cosmetics, medical equipment, medical consumables, industrial chemicals, pesticides, fuel, air conditioners, kitchen equipment, and sanitary ware products. The company also engages in the civil engineering planning and designing, implementation, and supervision business, as well as decoration and cleaning of structure activities. Kanda Holdings Co.,Ltd. was founded in 1943 and is headquartered in Tokyo, Japan.
